On jungle Jax, Xin and Trundle I always go BoRK/devourer then full tank:

{{champion:24}} {{champion:5}} {{champion:48}} 

{{item:3153}} {{item:3710}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3110}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3111}} 

this is because triforce is too expensive to rush on junglers while providing no sustain (especially important on Jax), doesn't have a slow and doesnt have scaling damage. In addition, Triforce falls off somewhat late game on these champs since they all have huge AS steroids, so eventually their autoattacks surpass their spellblade procs. Jax/Xin/Trundle with this build all surpass 2.0 attacks per second with their steroids maxed, and that is basically 3 autos in 1.5 seconsd = 1 spellblade proc. 3 autos on a 45 stack devourer late game (70 damage total) is 210 magic damage, which is stronger than the 230 or so physical damage from a triforce in that time.
